Q: What is the difference between the grid and the fluid-grid?
The grid reformat in quantum steps, whereas the fluid is ... well fluid.
That's it!
Now, the fluid model tries to take as much space as possible on the screen
The grid is formatted at a specific size, regarless of the screen.
It the browser display changes, the fluid design always attempts to take the max od real estate
while the grid is step for different format.
See @media in css
